# ─── Android packaging — PWABuilder / Bubblewrap / Google Play output ───
# These artifacts are generated outside the repo (typically via
# PWABuilder.com → "Package for Stores"). Two categories:
#
#   SENSITIVE (must NEVER be committed):
#     `signing.keystore` + `signing-key-info.txt` ARE the private signing
#     identity. Anyone with these can forge updates that install on top
#     of the legitimate app — and because Android refuses to install an
#     "update" signed with a different key, a leak forces a brand-new app
#     id and orphans every existing install. The general `*.keystore` /
#     `*.jks` / `signing-key-info.txt` patterns below catch any similar
#     file placed anywhere else in the tree as a safety net.
#
#   BUILD OUTPUTS:
#     `RDSWA.aab` (~3 MB) is the Google Play upload bundle and is
#     re-generated on every PWABuilder run, so it stays out of git.
#     `RDSWA.apk` is INTENTIONALLY committable (sideload distribution,
#     direct-download link from GitHub releases, etc.) — only the
#     specific `.aab` and signing files inside the folder are ignored,
#     not the folder itself.
#
# Keep the keystore + signing-key-info.txt backed up OFF-repo (password
# manager, encrypted Google Drive folder, offline USB) — losing them
# makes every future update of the published app impossible.
/rdswa.vercel.app - Google Play Package/signing.keystore
/rdswa.vercel.app - Google Play Package/signing-key-info.txt
/rdswa.vercel.app - Google Play Package/RDSWA.aab
*.keystore
*.jks
signing-key-info.txt
*.aab

